# .env.dev.template — reference: which env vars map to which AWS Secrets Manager paths.
#
# This is documentation, not a file to copy. For day-to-day work, just maintain your own .env.
#
# ONBOARDING / RESET ONLY: `./scripts/sync-dev-secrets.sh` pulls every env var listed below from
# AWS Secrets Manager into your local .env in one shot. Useful for setting up a fresh repo or
# resetting to the canonical shared values. WARNING: re-running OVERWRITES every managed key
# with whatever AWS currently holds — don't run it on a working .env if you have personal
# values you want to keep.
#
# Prerequisites for the sync script:
#   1. Set up the PangeaChat-Dev profile (see ../devops/.github/instructions/aws-iam-permissions.instructions.md → CLI Profile Setup).
#   2. Run `aws sso login --profile PangeaChat-Dev`.
#   3. Run `AWS_PROFILE=PangeaChat-Dev ./scripts/sync-dev-secrets.sh`.
#
# Anything not listed here stays untouched in your local .env — set those manually.

# --- Shared staging_automated_tests Matrix account (for Playwright + manual auth flows) ---
TEST_MATRIX_USERNAME=               # /staging/test-user/matrix-credentials#username
TEST_MATRIX_PASSWORD=               # /staging/test-user/matrix-credentials#password
